Rules:
- Fuse clusters that are the same person by context, role, and aliases — not just by literal name. When you fuse, union their aliases.
- The merged `name` is the MOST-USED canonical form. Use Title Case (e.g. "Frog-faced Doctor", not "doctor"). Move other forms into `aliases` (deduplicated).
- The merged `description` MUST combine the strongest evidence into 2-4 sentences. *Critically*, preserve any AFFILIATION (church, faction, organization, school, kingdom) and ORIGIN (nationality, birthplace, cultural heritage) cues from ANY cluster or prior volume — these are needed for downstream voice-casting and are easy to lose during summarization. Do not invent traits.
- Keep the strongest 2-3 pieces of evidence overall (prefer the most distinctive quotes, and quotes that justify affiliation/origin if such claims appear).
- Drop a cluster only when its `chapters` count is 1 AND it has no spoken dialogue AND performs no significant action.

Return JSON only.

